<span id="freeTextContainer16129922421552175420">One. Flawless. Masterpiece! Bona fide.<br/><br/>As a reader you cannot ask for more. This dense and complex novel about the Trujillo Era in the D.R., like the best novels, from &quot;Gone with the Wind&quot; to &quot;The Human Stain,&quot; explains not only the steps leading to a total devastation, but, braver still, its equally about the eventual aftermath. &quot;The Feast of the Goat&quot; is unputdownable, remarkable. A sturdy and sure classic. Read THIS!<br/><br/>Not much more can be said, without sounding as though I am somehow WORTHY of e</span>
  <span id="freeText16129922421552175420" style="display:none">One. Flawless. Masterpiece! Bona fide.<br /><br />As a reader you cannot ask for more. This dense and complex novel about the Trujillo Era in the D.R., like the best novels, from "Gone with the Wind" to "The Human Stain," explains not only the steps leading to a total devastation, but, braver still, its equally about the eventual aftermath. "The Feast of the Goat" is unputdownable, remarkable. A sturdy and sure classic. Read THIS!<br /><br />Not much more can be said, without sounding as though I am somehow WORTHY of even critiquing this!!</span>
